<li id="c20">
  <div class="cx" id="cx51076805">
   <h5> <a class="de">&nbsp;</a><span class="cu">The problem is not the minimum wage</span>


<span class="crd ntb">(<a href="/comments/1231497/51076805#c20?mode=alone;showrate=1#c20">0+ / 0-</a>)</span>
  </h5>

  
  


  

  <div class="ct">
  
<p>the problem is there aren't enough jobs anymore that can feed a family, provide health insurance, etc. Fast food work <em>should</em> be minimum wage. It's an entry level job, even for "Sandwich Experts." God bless them, but they're taking jobs from your sixteen-year-old neighbor. The 28 year old's real job was shipped to China, Vietnam or Latin America. The major failure of American capitalism is its sellout to unrestricted free market capitalism; with the Pan Pacific Treaty capitalism will fail America completely. Minimum wage treats the symptom, not the disease.</p>

  </div>
  <div class="cf">
  <p class="sig"></p>
  <p class="cb">by <a href="/user/uid:973106">Mike732</a> on <a href="/comments/1231497/51076805#c20">Sun Aug 18, 2013 at 09:10:47 AM PDT</a></p>
